        {
          "termNumber": 3,
          "term": "Term 3",
          "lessons": [
            {
              "lessonId": "recszOBluFVOSxnSg",
              "termNumber": 3,
              "termLabel": "Term 3",
              "weekNumber": 25,
              "weekLabel": "Week 1",
              "sequence": 25,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 25",
              "title": "25m Canadian Government: Grade 7 - Lesson 25",
              "body": "Introduction to Three Levels of Government\n\n➜ INTRO\nThis term, you will learn more about the three levels of government for your own area. This will require independent online research, so be sure to consult with your parent or teacher. \n\n➜ REFLECT\nBefore looking anything up, can you name the three levels of government? Do you remember the titles of the heads of each level, and do you know the names of the individuals who fill these roles in your local area?\n\n➜ VIEW\n∞ Video Link: Levels of Government (Video)\n\n➜ READ\n∞ Article Link: Levels of Government\n\n➜ NOTEBOOK\nDivide a blank page into three columns, and label each with the name of each level of government. Using the links below, enter in as much\ninformation as you can regarding the structure and responsibilities of each.\n➜ EXPLORE\nTest your knowledge with the following activities. If you run out of time today, you can test your knowledge during the next lesson.\n∞ Link: Activity: Levels of Government\n∞ Link: Around Town Game: Levels of Government",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recIVyFFuzbJhFIAy&6J82c=recszOBluFVOSxnSg",
              "links": [
                {
                  "text": "Levels of Government (Video)",
                  "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uwcMDuSGym4"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Levels of Government",
                  "url": "https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/settle-canada/government.html"
